Kadane's Algorithm : Maximum Subarray Sum in an Array
Problem Statement: Given an integer array nums, find the subarray with the largest sum and return the sum of the elements present in that subarray.

A subarray is a contiguous non-empty sequence of elements within an array.

solution: 
class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
        int cs = nums[0]; 
        int ms = nums[0]; 

        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
            cs = Math.max(nums[i], cs + nums[i]); 
            ms = Math.max(ms, cs); 
        }

        return ms;
    }
}

Maximum Product Subarray in an Array
Problem Statement: Given an array that contains both negative and positive integers, find the maximum product subarray. 
solution:
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {

        int maxProd = nums[0];
        int minProd = nums[0];
        int ans = nums[0];

        for(int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int curr = nums[i];

            int tempMax = Math.max(
                curr,
                Math.max(maxProd * curr, minProd * curr)
            );

            int tempMin = Math.min(
                curr,
                Math.min(maxProd * curr, minProd * curr)
            );

            maxProd = tempMax;
            minProd = tempMin;

            ans = Math.max(ans, maxProd);
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
